<br>
In case you don't know, news from a LOT of sources end up<br>
on the AP wire. <br>
(I've found Yahoo news the fastest way to check the AP<br>
feeds.)<br>
<br>
Virtually ALL newspapers in the country subscribe to AP<br>
service, which IS 24 hours.<br>
(I was on the phone with someone late at night at a<br>
newspaper office, and waited as the AP feed updated with<br>
a new story.)<br>
<br>
That means every newspaper you can buy, every tv news<br>
program you can watch, every radio news station, gets <br>
everything on the AP.  Most reputable online news sources<br>
would, also.  <br>
<br>
<br>
If it MADE it onto the AP wire, it is a legitimate news story.<br>
If it did, it went EVERYWHERE.  I'll check my own online<br>
news headlines and see what I find.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frostwraith>Frost Wraith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#B87333>(10/4/03 9:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weapons of Mass Destruction??</span><hr size=1> I would also like to point out that they said chemical weapons and biological *WARHEADS*....not the actual stuff. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">-----------------------------------------------</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
